Gulf and Western Inc's publishing unit,Simon and Schuster, said it agreed in principle to acquire&lt;Woodhead-Faulkner (Publishers) Ltd>, a British-based publisherof professional and consumer books, for undisclosed terms.    Upon completion of the proposed transaction,Woodhead-Faulkner will become part of Simon and Schuster'sInternational Group, which in the U.K. includes Simon andSchuster trade books, and Prentice Hall academic texts.    Simon and Schuster said that Woodhead-Faulkner willcontinue to publish under that name.    The company will continue to be under the direction ofMartin Woodhead, who will report to Henry Hirschberg, presidentof Simon and Schuster's International Group.    Woodhead-Faulkner, founded in 1972, publishes internationalbanking, finance, and investment books. Reuter&#3;